&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How to apply&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We usually receive a large number of applications, and our goal is to follow up with you within two weeks. You’ll hear from us either way. Here’s what you can expect from the rest of our hiring process:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A phone screen with our recruiter&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hiring manager screen&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working session with the team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’ll keep you informed through every step. To get started, complete this application, including a cover letter and answers to the questions on the next page. We read every single application, and your cover letter and responses help put your experience into context.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kit is an equal opportunity employer. We value diversity in all of its forms, and we hire the best person we can for each role, no matter your personal background. Research tells us that applicants who are female or non-binary, as well as applicants who are people of color, are less likely to apply for roles they do not feel 100% qualified for. If you think you meet more than 50% of our requirements but fewer than 100% of them, please apply. We’re imperfect communicators, so think of our job postings as the starting point for discussion rather than proof that you shouldn’t apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kit does not discriminate on the basis of race, sex, color, religion, age, national origin, marital status, disability, veteran status, genetic information, sexual orientation, gender identity or any other reason prohibited by law in provision of employment opportunities and benefits.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h4&gt;Description&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;Kit is an email-first operating system for creators who mean business. We help creators grow and monetize their audience with ease. For coaches, YouTubers, authors, podcasters, and other creatives, there isn’t a better marketing hub to rely on to grow audiences, automate email marketing, and sell digital products - all within one platform. More importantly, there isn’t a team more committed to helping creators earn a living.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re on a mission to help creators earn $1 billion using our creator marketing platform. We have always been 100% independent and 100% remote. We are proud to have built a product that our customers love, and we look for people who have enthusiasm and belief in our mission, vision, and values to join our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Kit culture is one where emotional intelligence is valued, radical candor is encouraged, and where everyone works together to uphold a set of shared team principles.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re hiring a Senior Financial Analyst to own our financial forecasting and bring sharp, strategic insight to every corner of the business. This is a high-autonomy, high-impact individual contributor role that supports our Head of Finance in partnering with the exec team on forward-looking analysis that drives real decisions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re a SaaS platform, so metrics like MRR, LTV, CAC, and activation are core to how we operate. If those are second nature to you, keep reading. You’ll connect the dots between those levers and their revenue impact—turning pricing, retention, and growth signals into forecasts the business can actually use. You’ll also work closely with our Data team to uplevel how we use metrics to guide the business.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your support system&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll report to&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.linkedin.com/in/anthonywakim/&quot;&gt;Anthony Wakim&lt;/a&gt;, our Head of Finance. He’ll help you ramp, set context, and be a sounding board—but this role is all about ownership. You’ll lead forecasting, reporting, and decision support from the start.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We keep our in-house finance team lean (just two people), but you’ll have strong external partners on accounting and ops. You’ll also have access to our full finance stack (Runway, Stripe, Quicksite, QuickBooks), and tight collaboration with Product, Sales, Marketing, and Data.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;First week:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Get oriented on Kit’s business model, customer segments, and SaaS metrics. Meet your manager and key partners across Product, Marketing, Sales, and Data. Audit our existing reports, forecasts, and dashboards. Shadow our monthly forecasting cycle. Complete a quick breakeven analysis to support pricing and margin decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;First month:&lt;/strong&gt; Start contributing to forecast updates. Collaborate with cross-functional teams to refine assumptions, track trends, and sharpen insights. Support exec-level financial narratives and scenario modeling to guide key business decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;First six months: &lt;/strong&gt;Partner with Data to level up finance dashboards. Build models that map growth levers—like activation, retention, pricing, and CAC efficiency—directly to revenue and profitability. Run pricing simulations, model activation improvements on MRR and retention, and assess plan-level margin across customer segments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;First year:&lt;/strong&gt; Help evolve Kit’s operating model to support scale. Maintain financial frameworks that connect metrics to revenue, headcount, and unit economics. Partner with the Head of Finance to strengthen forecast accuracy and decision-making tools. Support GTM strategy through CAC payback modeling, discounting analysis, and performance insights across channels and segments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What will set you up for success&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’ve built your own forecasting models—and know how to pressure test them&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You think in systems, not just spreadsheets&lt;/li&gt;
